# Deployment and operations

## Local development

- Requirements: Node >= 24.14, PNPM, Docker
- Start dependencies: docker compose up -d (MySQL on 3309, Redis on 6380)
- Generate Prisma: pnpm --filter dineros-app exec prisma generate
- Run dev: pnpm dev

Devcontainer option: .devcontainer/docker-compose.yml sets up MySQL/Redis in a devcontainer scenario with DATABASE_URL override.

## Containers

- App image: app/Dockerfile
  - Multi-stage: pnpm fetch → prisma generate (placeholder DATABASE_URL) → nuxt build → runner with .output
  - Exposes PORT (default 3000 in local; 80 in k8s via env)
- Microservice image: microservice/Dockerfile
  - Generates prisma client, runs H3 server via pnpm start; alternate target runner-keyrotate for CronJob utilities

## CI pipelines (GitHub Actions)

- PR workflow (.github/workflows/pr.yml)
  - Lint, Vitest, pre-commit security, CodeQL
  - If PR from same repo, build app and microservice images tagged pr-<N>-<SHA> and deploy to staging GKE via .deploy/dineros.template.yaml (profile=staging)
  - Verify rollout, call health readiness endpoint
  - Optional: request Cursor Bugbot comment
- Main workflow (.github/workflows/main.yml)
  - On push to main/master: build/push images with latest and SHA tags; deploy to production GKE; verify rollout + readiness
- CodeQL scheduled weekly workflow also present
- SonarQube manual workflow provided (sonar.yml)

## Kubernetes manifests

- Template: .deploy/dineros.template.yaml (render with envsubst using profile env in .deploy/profiles/*)
- Deploys two Deployments (app and microservice), Services, and an Ingress
- Secrets
  - Database URL provided via separate Secret names for app and microservice
  - DB field-encryption key material provided via ${SECRET_DB}
  - App secrets (JWT, OpenAI, Postmark, Plaid, INTERNAL_API_TOKEN) via ${SECRET_APP}/${SECRET_JWT}
- Health probes configured against /health/live and /health/ready

## Key rotation CronJob (staging)

- .deploy/key-rotation-cronjob.template.yaml builds with microservice image target runner-keyrotate
- Requires Role/RoleBinding in .deploy/key-rotation-rbac.template.yaml (apply with sufficient GKE IAM)
- Script microservice/scripts/k8s-rotate-db-key.sh:
  - Patches Secret holding DB encryption keys (append-only), restarts Deployments to pick up env, then calls microservice migrate route

## Verification

- verify-dineros-gke-deploy.sh checks kubectl rollout and public readiness URL per environment

## Notes

- Images are pushed to gcr.io/${GCP_PROJECT_ID}
- The microservice listens on port 3050 in k8s (ClusterIP service)
- SHOW_BULL_MQ_ADMIN is false in production manifests
